text.tspan: Sweden: Daily new confirmed COVID-19 deaths, by date of death, Sweden,
Shown is the rolling 7-day average, reported by date of death. Because it takes a number of days until all deaths for a particular
day are reported in Sweden, death counts for the last 2 weeks must only be interpreted as an incomplete measure of mortality.
Source: Swedish Public Health Agency Last updated 10 March 2023
